%I A321571 #22 Mar 20 2026 04:08:08
%S A321571 2,6,342,137186159382,
%T A321571 20574018325197218999594988949603700627255750813932694467611442806
%N A321571 a(n) is the order of the free linear Heyting algebra on n generators.
%C A321571 a(7) has 4016 digits and so is too long to be included. - _Miles Englezou_, Mar 08 2026
%H A321571 Miles Englezou, <a href="/A321571/b321571.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..6</a>
%H A321571 Peter Freyd, <a href="https://www2.math.upenn.edu/~pjf/Heyting.pdf">On the size of Heyting Semi-Lattices and Equationally Linear Heyting Algebras</a>, Jul 17 2017.
%F A321571 a(n) = (b(n-1) + 1)*b(n-1), where b(n) = Product_{r=0..n-1} (b(r) + 1)^binomial(n,r). - _Miles Englezou_, Mar 08 2026
%o A321571 (PARI) a(n) = (b(n) = prod(r = 0, n-1, (1+b(r))^binomial(n,r))); (b(n-1)+1)*b(n-1) \\ _Miles Englezou_, Mar 08 2026
